                <td bgcolor="#ECECEC" valign="top" width="100%"><font color="#000000" face="arial" size="2"><small>Posted&nbsp;-&nbsp;09/25/2003&nbsp;: 5:39:49 PM</small><hr size="2"><span class="spnMessageText"> Nobody loves a good discussion better than I do.  In a recent thread arguing about governmental issues, someone brought up the topic of abortion and the "right to live".<br /><br /><blockquote id="quote"><font size="2" face="arial" id="quote">quote:<hr height="1" noshade id="quote"><i>Kebkek wrote</i><br /><br />I'm going out on a limb here, but you probaly belive its just for a woman to have the right to choose whether or not her unborn child should be allowed to be born, while also commending the Prosecuters in California on the double murder charge against Scott Peterson on the murder of his unborn child.. Am I wrong? I use this example because it illustrates the hipocracy of MEN in deciding the fate of human beings right to life and death. I am not a religous person at all.. so debate me on the merits of my arguement all you want, but before you do, understand I am not preaching from the religous right, but as a guy who just thinks Men/woman don't have the right to choose life or death at all.<br /><hr height="1" noshade id="quote"></blockquote id="quote"></font id="quote"><br /><br />I couldn't really see how it was relevant to the topic at hand, but I did think it would make a great thread topic all on its own.<br /><br />The paragraph wasn't directed at me, so instead of replying to its points, I'll just give my opinion on the abortion issue.<br /><br />I <b>do</b> believe that a woman should have the right to have an abortion.  Where the issue becomes gray for me is <i>timing</i>.  How late is too late?  What trimester of the pregnancy?  To me, taking it too far leads to the Catholic point of view, wherby even contraception is considered a no-no.  Of course taking it to Drex levels, we could even go farther saying that not hitting on women is bad because you're destroying a potential life by not getting laid by that hottie at the bar.  But that's just getting silly, isn't it?<br /><br />I support a woman's right to have an abortion if her child has a defect, heck, I'm in support of genetic engineering to keep children from having defects (yes, I've seen <i>Gattica</i>, and I've read <i>Brave New World</i>, no need to explain them to me).  <br /><br />I think I'll pretty much leave my statements at that, and we'll see how far it progresses from here.<br /><br /></span></font></td>
