irst breath<br /><br />B. Because in this case the law specifically DOESN'T err on the side of life, which I believe it always should. The mother didn't take active steps to protect the health of the baby. Blissful negligence shouldn't be a defense.<br /><br />There seems more evidence she neglected the babies right to live than there is evidence that she didn't actually kill it outright<br /></span></font></td>
